Now I have enough context. Let me set up todos and implement the component.

`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- The water shader uses `pos.xz` for wave direction, so the mesh needs vertices in XZ (not XY). `TerrainChunks` builds a custom XZ `BufferGeometry` for this reason. Using `THREE.PlaneGeometry` (XY) with a `-π/2` X rotation keeps the shader working — local `pos.y` becomes world `Z`, meaning wave propagation uses `(localX, 0)` but still produces visible displacement.
- The imperative `useFrame` + `Map<id, mesh>` pattern (used by TerrainChunks and StaticInstances) enables zero React re-renders per frame while correctly tracking entity lifecycle.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`
